
[1]antanagoge

   ANTANAGO'GE, n. antanago'gy. [Gr. against, and a taking up.]

   In rhetoric, a figure which consists in replying to an adversary, by
   way of recrimination; as, when the accusation of one party is
   unanswerable, the accused person charges him with the same or other
   crime.
